1
00:00:06,124 --> 00:00:08,724
I didn't think that it wouldn't be around anymore.

2
00:00:08,724 --> 00:00:11,024
I hear they're going to build a condominium.

3
00:00:11,024 --> 00:00:13,624
Too bad, because it was a delicious diner.

4
00:00:13,624 --> 00:00:15,524
Too bad.

5
00:00:15,524 --> 00:00:17,924
Well, let's go, then.

6
00:00:17,924 --> 00:00:19,024
Come to think of it,

7
00:00:19,024 --> 00:00:22,224
there are a lot of new buildings being constructed around here.

8
00:00:22,224 --> 00:00:23,924
Over there, too.

9
00:00:23,924 --> 00:00:26,824
Yes, that used to be a sweet dumplings shop.

10
00:00:26,824 --> 00:00:28,024
Over there, too.

11
00:00:28,024 --> 00:00:30,724
There used to be an old apartment there.

12
00:00:30,724 --> 00:00:31,924
There, too.

13
00:00:31,924 --> 00:00:34,424
That used to be a bookstore, I think.

14
00:00:34,424 --> 00:00:35,824
Over here, too.

15
00:00:35,824 --> 00:00:37,824
Take a good look. They're renovating the place.

16
00:00:39,324 --> 00:00:41,224
Over here, too.

17
00:00:41,224 --> 00:00:42,624
What about here?

18
00:00:42,624 --> 00:00:44,924
This was an old public bath house.

19
00:00:44,924 --> 00:00:47,224
I came here a few times, too.

20
00:00:47,224 --> 00:00:50,824
It looks like this place is going to be a facility for bathing.

21
00:00:50,824 --> 00:00:52,224
Gosh.

22
00:00:52,224 --> 00:00:54,924
If so, they should've just left it as is a bath house.

23
00:00:54,924 --> 00:00:56,624
You can say that again.

24
00:00:56,624 --> 00:01:00,024
I guess that's what they call business.

25
00:01:00,024 --> 00:01:02,224
But it's sort of sad to think that

26
00:01:02,224 --> 00:01:03,924
things from the past are disappearing.

27
00:01:03,924 --> 00:01:05,324
I guess so.

28
00:01:12,524 --> 00:01:14,024
What's the matter?

29
00:01:19,424 --> 00:01:22,424
Somebody, call an ambulance!

30
00:01:22,424 --> 00:01:24,724
-Ran, get an ambulance! -Yes, sir.

31
00:01:24,724 --> 00:01:26,824
Mr. Inomata's not here.

32
00:01:26,824 --> 00:01:30,524
He was in the smoking room a while ago, so maybe...

33
00:01:30,524 --> 00:01:31,524
Darn it.

34
00:01:31,524 --> 00:01:33,324
Mr. Murase, hurry up!

35
00:01:33,324 --> 00:01:34,824
Yes, sir.

36
00:01:48,624 --> 00:01:50,324
Aiming for a 100% solution.

37
00:01:50,324 --> 00:01:52,524
Clear all mysteries and codes.

38
00:01:52,524 --> 00:01:54,324
Shocking sound at a construction site!

39
00:01:54,324 --> 00:01:56,224
An awesome deadly trick is schemed.

40
00:01:56,224 --> 00:01:57,824
He sees through the one and only truth.

41
00:01:57,824 --> 00:01:59,924
A child in appearance with the I.Q. of an adult.

42
00:01:59,924 --> 00:02:02,324
His name is Detective Conan!

43
00:03:46,788 --> 00:03:52,588
"Unidentified Impact"

44
00:03:53,088 --> 00:03:55,388
Okay, give me an outline of this case.

45
00:03:55,388 --> 00:03:56,488
Yes, sir.

46
00:03:56,488 --> 00:03:59,488
At about noon today, there was an accident

47
00:03:59,488 --> 00:04:02,788
in which the pipes that are used as footings collapsed.

48
00:04:02,788 --> 00:04:05,888
The victim is Mr. Yuji Inomata, age 56.

49
00:04:05,888 --> 00:04:08,388
He seems to be the owner of this site.

50
00:04:08,388 --> 00:04:10,988
The cause of death is bruises all over his body

51
00:04:10,988 --> 00:04:12,388
due to being buried under collapsed pipes.

52
00:04:12,388 --> 00:04:15,088
They say that it is most likely that he died instantly.

53
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:16,288
Inspector.

54
00:04:16,288 --> 00:04:17,988
There was a trace on the band bunching the pipes together.

55
00:04:17,988 --> 00:04:21,388
Someone deliberately making a slit on it.

56
00:04:21,388 --> 00:04:22,788
I think would be reasonable to say that

57
00:04:22,788 --> 00:04:26,988
this is a homicide rather than an accident.

58
00:04:26,988 --> 00:04:30,688
But I wonder why Mr. Inomata was there?

59
00:04:30,688 --> 00:04:33,688
There was an ashtray under the pipes that were collapsed.

60
00:04:33,688 --> 00:04:36,588
Maybe it was the smoking area or something?

61
00:04:36,588 --> 00:04:38,388
The smoking area?

62
00:04:38,388 --> 00:04:39,688
I see.

63
00:04:39,688 --> 00:04:41,988
Come to think of it, there were cigarette butts

64
00:04:41,988 --> 00:04:44,588
found at the feet of the victim.

65
00:04:44,588 --> 00:04:47,888
Mr. Inomata was a heavy smoker.

66
00:04:47,888 --> 00:04:50,988
Anytime he had time, he'd go to take a puff.

67
00:04:50,988 --> 00:04:54,288
They are people who were at the scene when the accident occurred.

68
00:04:54,288 --> 00:04:56,788
They're all personnel of this construction site.

69
00:04:56,788 --> 00:05:01,188
He's Mr. Inomata's chauffeur, Mr. Masao Kaneda.

70
00:05:01,188 --> 00:05:05,988
He's Mr. Takeshi Nojima, the construction director of this site.

71
00:05:05,988 --> 00:05:08,988
And he's Mr. Naoki Murase, an architect.

72
00:05:08,988 --> 00:05:11,488
He seems to be in charge of designing this place.

73
00:05:11,488 --> 00:05:15,488
Will you tell me your circumstances just before the accident?

74
00:05:15,488 --> 00:05:17,688
Back then, I was told by Mr. Inomata

75
00:05:17,688 --> 00:05:20,788
to go buy coffee or something for the guest.

76
00:05:20,788 --> 00:05:24,688
I went to the vending machine behind the site to buy coffee.

77
00:05:24,688 --> 00:05:28,388
When I got back, the pipes were collapsed.

78
00:05:28,388 --> 00:05:31,188
Who was that guest?

79
00:05:31,188 --> 00:05:33,088
It's me.

80
00:05:33,088 --> 00:05:36,288
I came to talk out about details.

81
00:05:36,288 --> 00:05:38,288
Details?

82
00:05:38,288 --> 00:05:40,488
Rather, I came to discuss

83
00:05:40,488 --> 00:05:41,888
the concept of the setting of this place.

84
00:05:41,888 --> 00:05:45,488
And while Mr. Kaneda was out buying coffee,

85
00:05:45,488 --> 00:05:48,488
I decided to call my office.

86
00:05:48,488 --> 00:05:49,588
During that time,

87
00:05:49,588 --> 00:05:52,788
Mr. Inomata left for the smoking area to take a puff.

88
00:05:52,788 --> 00:05:55,688
After a while, I heard a loud noise.

89
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:58,088
I looked towards the smoking area...

90
00:05:58,088 --> 00:06:00,588
I was on lunch break,

91
00:06:00,588 --> 00:06:02,888
so I was here at the office.

92
00:06:02,888 --> 00:06:06,088
Then, I heard a loud noise.

93
00:06:06,088 --> 00:06:08,988
So you all came here

94
00:06:08,988 --> 00:06:11,488
since you heard the loud noise, right?

95
00:06:11,488 --> 00:06:14,688
No one saw the pipes was collapsing?

96
00:06:14,688 --> 00:06:18,288
Is this an accident?

97
00:06:18,288 --> 00:06:19,988
Or maybe...

98
00:06:19,988 --> 00:06:23,988
We haven't put aside the possibility of homicide yet.

99
00:06:26,888 --> 00:06:29,688
If I remember correctly,

100
00:06:29,688 --> 00:06:32,788
Mr. Kaneda borrowed money from Mr. Inomata.

101
00:06:32,788 --> 00:06:33,788
What the...

102
00:06:33,788 --> 00:06:36,188
The other day, I heard Mr. Kaneda say

103
00:06:36,188 --> 00:06:40,988
that if Inomata disappears, he can call it a wash.

104
00:06:40,988 --> 00:06:42,788
Hey, hold on!

105
00:06:42,788 --> 00:06:45,188
It's true that I did say that.

106
00:06:45,188 --> 00:06:48,788
It was because I was a bit pissed back then.

107
00:06:48,788 --> 00:06:50,688
What makes you think that I'd go as far as to kill somebody

108
00:06:50,688 --> 00:06:52,088
just because of something like that?

109
00:06:52,088 --> 00:06:55,688
I think you would.

110
00:06:55,688 --> 00:06:58,888
If so, then you're just as prone to, aren't you?

111
00:06:58,888 --> 00:07:00,588
You were arguing with Inomata

112
00:07:00,588 --> 00:07:03,088
on whether to lower or higher the architectural fee, weren't you?

113
00:07:03,088 --> 00:07:05,688
That's right. You're the one who specified

114
00:07:05,688 --> 00:07:07,388
that place to be the smoking area too, right?

115
00:07:07,388 --> 00:07:09,388
You specified that place so that you could

116
00:07:09,388 --> 00:07:10,388
take your grudge out on Mr. Inomata, didn't you?

117
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:12,988
I have no grudge against Mr. Inomata.

118
00:07:12,988 --> 00:07:14,988
Don't play dumb with me!

119
00:07:14,988 --> 00:07:17,688
Mr. Kaneda, calm down.

120
00:07:18,788 --> 00:07:21,788
Come to think of it, you're to be suspected too.

121
00:07:21,788 --> 00:07:24,088
You were angry after Mr. Inomata turned

122
00:07:24,088 --> 00:07:26,688
your concept of the plan down many times.

123
00:07:26,688 --> 00:07:29,988
No. I would never do that.

124
00:07:29,988 --> 00:07:33,888
Well, calm down, everyone.

125
00:07:33,888 --> 00:07:36,688
At any rate, I didn't do it.

126
00:07:40,888 --> 00:07:43,588
Inspector Megure.

127
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:46,688
From the blade of the knife that was found,

128
00:07:46,688 --> 00:07:48,288
a band made of the same nylon

129
00:07:48,288 --> 00:07:50,888
that was holding the pipes together was found.

130
00:07:50,888 --> 00:07:52,688
Judging from the way the substance was stuck on,

131
00:07:52,688 --> 00:07:54,788
there's seems to be no mistake

132
00:07:54,788 --> 00:07:57,188
that the band was severed with this knife.

133
00:07:57,188 --> 00:07:58,988
Good work.

134
00:08:00,988 --> 00:08:03,488
Well, so this is it.

135
00:08:03,488 --> 00:08:05,288
The culprit is Mr. Kaneda.

136
00:08:05,288 --> 00:08:06,588
It's you.

137
00:08:06,588 --> 00:08:08,288
Why me?

138
00:08:08,288 --> 00:08:10,788
There's no use to play dumb.

139
00:08:10,788 --> 00:08:12,688
This is yours, isn't it?

140
00:08:12,688 --> 00:08:15,488
Your name is carved on it.

141
00:08:15,488 --> 00:08:19,088
After Mr. Murase went outside to receive a phone call,

142
00:08:19,088 --> 00:08:21,588
you pretended to go out to buy coffee

143
00:08:21,588 --> 00:08:23,788
and went around behind where the pipes were stored.

144
00:08:23,788 --> 00:08:25,288
You used the knife that you had with you

145
00:08:25,288 --> 00:08:29,188
to cut the band that was holding the pipes together.

146
00:08:29,188 --> 00:08:31,588
And after the pipes collapsed,

147
00:08:31,588 --> 00:08:33,588
you ran over to the site of the accident

148
00:08:33,588 --> 00:08:34,788
as if you knew nothing of it.

149
00:08:34,788 --> 00:08:37,688
-But I don't think that was possible. -What?

150
00:08:37,688 --> 00:08:40,888
Because out of all the pipes that were bundled together,

151
00:08:40,888 --> 00:08:44,788
only the pipes nearest to the smoking area were collapsed.

152
00:08:44,788 --> 00:08:45,988
There seems to be no space

153
00:08:45,988 --> 00:08:49,688
for anyone to hide in an arm's reach, you see.

154
00:08:49,688 --> 00:08:51,488
And yet, if the band holding the pipes together

155
00:08:51,488 --> 00:08:52,588
were cut from smoking area side,

156
00:08:52,588 --> 00:08:54,588
it would be in clear view from Mr. Inomata.

157
00:08:54,588 --> 00:08:55,988
First of all, the culprit would also be at risk

158
00:08:55,988 --> 00:08:57,588
of being struck by the pipes.

159
00:08:57,588 --> 00:08:59,588
-So... -Shut up!

160
00:08:59,588 --> 00:09:01,888
The culprit somehow managed to follow through.

161
00:09:01,888 --> 00:09:03,688
How he managed it?

162
00:09:03,688 --> 00:09:05,188
At any rate,

163
00:09:05,188 --> 00:09:08,188
there's no doubt that Kaneda is the culprit.

164
00:09:08,188 --> 00:09:11,088
The knife at the site is immovable evidence.

165
00:09:11,088 --> 00:09:14,588
Wrong. I lost it yesterday.

166
00:09:14,588 --> 00:09:18,288
You can make up an excuse like that any way you want.

167
00:09:18,288 --> 00:09:19,888
Then, Mr. Kaneda,

168
00:09:19,888 --> 00:09:21,088
would you please tell us about your knife

169
00:09:21,088 --> 00:09:24,188
as well as some other details?

170
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:25,988
I don't mind.

171
00:09:25,988 --> 00:09:27,888
But I'm telling you, I didn't do it.

172
00:09:27,888 --> 00:09:31,388
May I excuse myself to go to the restroom?

173
00:09:31,388 --> 00:09:34,088
I would like to make a call to my office.

174
00:09:34,088 --> 00:09:35,188
All right.

175
00:09:35,188 --> 00:09:37,888
I'd like to also talk to you two later,

176
00:09:37,888 --> 00:09:40,188
so please don't leave the premises.

177
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:50,888
Even from what the forensics came up,

178
00:09:50,888 --> 00:09:52,488
there's no doubt about the fact

179
00:09:52,488 --> 00:09:54,888
that the band was cut with that knife.

180
00:09:54,888 --> 00:09:57,288
But I wonder if anyone would risk doing something like that

181
00:09:57,288 --> 00:09:59,488
knowing that he would also be endangering himself.

182
00:09:59,488 --> 00:10:01,688
Besides, the sound back then...

183
00:10:07,088 --> 00:10:08,388
This is...

184
00:10:38,488 --> 00:10:41,288
Sir, what's this?

185
00:10:41,288 --> 00:10:42,988
Oh, that?

186
00:10:42,988 --> 00:10:45,888
That's the plan of the concept

187
00:10:45,888 --> 00:10:48,088
that Mr. Murase showed Mr. Inomata.

188
00:10:48,088 --> 00:10:52,088
But he seems to have thrown it away after it was turned down.

189
00:10:52,088 --> 00:10:53,788
Isn't that the tile picture

190
00:10:53,788 --> 00:10:55,688
that was in the public bath that used to be here?

191
00:10:55,688 --> 00:10:57,188
It used to be in the bath tub

192
00:10:57,188 --> 00:11:00,388
and looked like there was a real carp inside.

193
00:11:00,388 --> 00:11:03,088
The men's restroom. Men's restroom.

194
00:11:03,088 --> 00:11:06,088
Conan, there you are.

195
00:11:06,088 --> 00:11:08,388
Stay put because it's dangerous.

196
00:11:08,388 --> 00:11:10,988
Ran. I have to go to the restroom,

197
00:11:10,988 --> 00:11:13,588
but Pops is in there now.

198
00:11:15,688 --> 00:11:19,288
I'm so sorry to have to trouble you like this suddenly.

199
00:11:19,288 --> 00:11:22,088
No problem at all.

200
00:11:22,088 --> 00:11:24,188
Thank you, director.

201
00:11:25,088 --> 00:11:27,588
Conan, are you all right?

202
00:11:27,588 --> 00:11:28,988
Are you all right?

203
00:11:28,988 --> 00:11:30,688
I'm sorry that it's slippery here

204
00:11:30,688 --> 00:11:33,088
since the floor's just been waxed.

205
00:11:33,088 --> 00:11:36,288
No, not at all. We're sorry for troubling you.

206
00:11:38,288 --> 00:11:40,988
May I buy a bottle of tea at the vending machine?

207
00:11:40,988 --> 00:11:42,788
Sure. I don't mind the least bit.

208
00:11:42,788 --> 00:11:44,788
Go right ahead.

209
00:11:47,188 --> 00:11:49,088
Huh? It's tepid.

210
00:11:49,088 --> 00:11:51,488
It's still being cooled, I guess.

211
00:11:51,488 --> 00:11:52,688
See.

212
00:11:52,688 --> 00:11:54,788
"Cooling" -That's true.

213
00:11:54,788 --> 00:11:55,888
Huh?

214
00:11:55,888 --> 00:11:59,488
Did the vending machine man come today?

215
00:11:59,488 --> 00:12:03,488
No. We're not doing business today because of renovations.

216
00:12:03,488 --> 00:12:05,388
Director, could I speak to you for a minute?

217
00:12:05,388 --> 00:12:07,488
Yes, I'll be right over.

218
00:12:07,488 --> 00:12:09,788
I'll have to go.

219
00:12:09,788 --> 00:12:11,988
Come again and visit us after we open, okay?

220
00:12:11,988 --> 00:12:13,188
Sure.

221
00:12:13,188 --> 00:12:15,688
Okay, let's head back then.

222
00:12:15,688 --> 00:12:17,688
Hey, Conan.

223
00:12:17,688 --> 00:12:19,788
You'll fall again, you know.

224
00:12:21,788 --> 00:12:23,388
"Electrical room"

225
00:12:42,188 --> 00:12:43,988
This is...

226
00:12:43,988 --> 00:12:47,188
Conan. What's the matter?

227
00:12:47,188 --> 00:12:48,488
Conan?

228
00:13:04,738 --> 00:13:07,338
The fingerprints have been verified.

229
00:13:07,338 --> 00:13:11,138
The prints on the knife are undoubtedly Mr. Kaneda's.

230
00:13:14,838 --> 00:13:17,138
Good work.

231
00:13:17,138 --> 00:13:20,738
Then, we'll have Mr. Kaneda come with us to the station.

232
00:13:22,238 --> 00:13:23,638
Why did it turn up like this?

233
00:13:23,638 --> 00:13:27,638
May I return to the main office?

234
00:13:27,638 --> 00:13:28,838
Me, too.

235
00:13:28,838 --> 00:13:31,038
Well then, as to both of you,

236
00:13:31,038 --> 00:13:33,038
we'll be contacting you again if necessary.

237
00:13:33,038 --> 00:13:34,838
You may go for today.

238
00:13:34,838 --> 00:13:36,638
Thank you.

239
00:13:36,638 --> 00:13:38,138
Is he going voluntarily?

240
00:13:38,138 --> 00:13:41,238
I'm sorry, but could you bring the car around?

241
00:13:41,238 --> 00:13:42,938
Roger, sir.

242
00:13:44,338 --> 00:13:46,438
Officer Chiba.

243
00:13:46,438 --> 00:13:48,538
What is it, Conan?

244
00:13:51,938 --> 00:13:54,138
-Mr. Mouri? -Yes.

245
00:13:56,238 --> 00:13:59,238
Hey, enough already.

246
00:13:59,238 --> 00:14:01,138
I didn't do it, I tell you.

247
00:14:01,138 --> 00:14:05,138
We'll hear you out, all you want at the station.

248
00:14:10,238 --> 00:14:12,038
Dad?

249
00:14:13,938 --> 00:14:16,038
Please wait, everyone.

250
00:14:16,038 --> 00:14:18,538
Mr. Kaneda is not the culprit.

251
00:14:18,538 --> 00:14:21,638
Just what're you talking about, Mr. Mouri?

252
00:14:21,638 --> 00:14:23,938
His fingerprints were also found on the knife, you know.

253
00:14:23,938 --> 00:14:27,738
Besides, you even said that he was the culprit.

254
00:14:27,738 --> 00:14:30,038
It's true I did say that,

255
00:14:30,038 --> 00:14:33,738
but I'd like to revise all the deductions I made thus far.

256
00:14:33,738 --> 00:14:37,638
The culprit is among the people here.

257
00:14:37,638 --> 00:14:39,938
I thought it was strange

258
00:14:39,938 --> 00:14:43,038
that the knife would be left behind at the site.

259
00:14:43,038 --> 00:14:46,938
It's true that it's thinkable that the culprit may have dropped it.

260
00:14:46,938 --> 00:14:50,038
But if so, what should also be here is missing.

261
00:14:50,038 --> 00:14:51,838
What should also be here?

262
00:14:51,838 --> 00:14:53,438
What is that?

263
00:14:53,438 --> 00:14:55,138
Please take another good look

264
00:14:55,138 --> 00:14:58,638
at where the knife was found on the ground.

265
00:14:58,638 --> 00:15:01,238
Right near it is the ashtray.

