312
00:16:58,338 --> 00:17:01,438
Mr. Mouri, what is that certain something?

313
00:17:06,138 --> 00:17:07,638
This is...

314
00:17:07,638 --> 00:17:09,638
A pitching machine?

315
00:17:09,638 --> 00:17:11,938
Exactly.

316
00:17:11,938 --> 00:17:14,138
At around noon today when the incident occurred,

317
00:17:14,138 --> 00:17:16,938
the window of the prefab was open.

318
00:17:16,938 --> 00:17:19,038
When I confirmed further,

319
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,238
the amusement facility was undergoing renovation,

320
00:17:21,238 --> 00:17:24,138
so the door of the emergency door was also open.

321
00:17:24,138 --> 00:17:28,838
Neither the nets nor the glass was set up yet.

322
00:17:28,838 --> 00:17:31,338
In other words, at the time of the incident

323
00:17:31,338 --> 00:17:32,338
from the site where the pipes

324
00:17:32,338 --> 00:17:34,638
were to the pitching machine on the 2nd floor,

325
00:17:34,638 --> 00:17:37,638
a path was formed.

326
00:17:39,138 --> 00:17:42,038
The culprit probably set the pitching machine up beforehand

327
00:17:42,038 --> 00:17:43,938
to throwing position

328
00:17:43,938 --> 00:17:46,538
and turned down the breaker of the building.

329
00:17:46,538 --> 00:17:49,938
After confirming that Mr. Inomata was in the smoking area,

330
00:17:49,938 --> 00:17:52,138
he turned the breaker back on.

331
00:17:59,338 --> 00:18:02,238
In other words, the culprit used the impact of the ball

332
00:18:02,238 --> 00:18:04,738
